      "description": "Fix Docker Build Failure ‚Äî Missing `@rollup/rollup-linux-x64-musl` in Coolify Deployment\n\n**Root cause:** Vite/Rollup requires a platform-specific native binary. Alpine Linux (musl) needs `@rollup/rollup-linux-x64-musl`. Bun v1.2.23 resolves optional dependencies differently than npm, causing the package to be absent during `bun run build`.\n\n---\n\n**Fix options (pick one):**\n\n**Option A ‚Äî Add explicit dependency (fastest fix)**\nAdd to `package.json` `optionalDependencies`:\n```json\n\"optionalDependencies\": {\n  \"@rollup/rollup-linux-x64-musl\": \"^4.0.0\"\n}\n```\nThen re-run `bun install` and commit updated lockfile.\n\n**Option B ‚Äî Install directly in Dockerfile**\nBefore the build step:\n```dockerfile\nRUN bun add -d @rollup/rollup-linux-x64-musl\nRUN bun run build\n```\n\n**Option C ‚Äî Switch base image away from musl**\nChange build stage to a glibc-based image (e.g., `node:22-slim` or `debian:bookworm-slim`) and install `@rollup/rollup-linux-x64-gnu` instead.\n\n---\n\n**Fix Dockerfile secrets warnings (4 found):**\n\nReplace `ARG`/`ENV` for `OPENROUTER_API_KEY` and `VITE_OPENROUTER_API_KEY` with Docker BuildKit secrets:\n\n```dockerfile\n# Instead of ARG/ENV, use:\nRUN --mount=type=secret,id=openrouter_key \\\n    export VITE_OPENROUTER_API_KEY=$(cat /run/secrets/openrouter_key) && \\\n    bun run build\n```\n\nOr pass via Coolify's built-in secret injection at runtime rather than build time.\n\n---\n\n**Verification:**\n- `docker build .` exits with code 0\n- No `SecretsUsedInArgOrEnv` warnings\n- `bun run build` completes inside container\n- Production stage serves built assets correctly\n- Test locally with `docker build --no-cache` before deploying via Coolify",
